+# Manual Picker Centering And I18n Implementation Plan
+
+> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
+
+**Spec Path:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-19-manual-picker-centered-i18n-design.md`
+
+**Goal:** Make manual alarm wheels center-selected with faded neighbors, compact the interval `Weeks` picker layout, and move user-visible app copy into English and Chinese Android string resources.
+
+**Architecture:** Keep wheel mechanics in `AlarmEditorScreen.kt`, keep domain/ViewModel alarm behavior unchanged, and use Android resources at UI/Android adapter boundaries for static copy. Use test tags for stable tests so localized visible text does not become the only automation hook.
+
+**Tech Stack:** Kotlin, Jetpack Compose Material3, Android string resources, existing Gradle/JUnit/Compose test stack.
+
+## Global Constraints
+
+- Hour wheel values remain `0..23`; minute values remain `0..59`; interval week values remain `1..104`.
+- A wheel selection is the value aligned with the wheel center, not the last explicitly tapped item.
+- Wheel controls may still support tapping as a convenience, but tapping is not required to select a scrolled value.
+- Interval week layout is compact: the `Weeks` label and wheel share one horizontal row, and the wheel height is about two rows instead of the main time wheel height.
+- String resources must live in `app/src/main/res/values/strings.xml` for English and `app/src/main/res/values-zh/strings.xml` for Chinese.
+- Compose UI code must use `stringResource` or resource IDs for user-visible copy instead of hardcoded display strings.
+- Android notifications, notification channels, and ringtone picker titles must use `Context.getString(...)`.
+- Locale-sensitive weekday/date display inside composables must remain driven by `LocalConfiguration`, not `Locale.getDefault()`.
+- Do not change alarm scheduling, Room schema, AI prompt/parser/tool schema, model catalog, ringtone behavior, or repeat-rule domain contracts.
+
+---
+
+## File Map
