+# Manual Picker Centering And I18n Spec
+
+## Problem
+
+The manual alarm editor now uses wheel controls, but the interaction still behaves like a scrollable list whose visible item must be tapped manually. A phone alarm editor should keep the center item selected automatically, with nearby values fading away from the center. In interval repeat mode, the `Weeks` wheel also consumes too much vertical space because it sits below the interval date controls.
+
+The app also has user-visible English strings hardcoded in Compose screens, notifications, and guidance rows. Future text changes need to be replaceable by locale, and the first supported locales are English and Chinese.
+
+## Success
+
+- Manual hour, minute, and interval week wheels auto-select the centered value after scrolling without requiring a tap on the number.
+- Wheel center values are visually strongest, with neighboring values progressively muted above and below the center.
+- Interval mode places the compact `Weeks` wheel to the right of the `Weeks` label, not as a large block under the dates.
+- The interval week wheel shows roughly two numeric rows of height, with the centered number selected and surrounding numbers softened.
+- User-visible app text is backed by Android string resources for English and Chinese.
+- Existing alarm domain, scheduling, persistence, AI parser, and model behavior are unchanged.
+
+## Out Of Scope
+
+- Adding a new language beyond English and Chinese.
+- Adding an in-app language picker. Android resource locale selection is sufficient.
+- Changing alarm recurrence semantics, Room schema, OpenRouter prompts/tool schemas, or ringtone behavior.
+- Rewriting non-user-facing diagnostic, log, serialization, database, or network protocol strings.
+- Localizing model-generated or remote error reason text itself. The local prefix around such text should be resource-backed where it is shown to users.
+
+## Critical Paths
+
+1. Create and edit a manual alarm, scroll hour/minute wheels, and save the centered selected values.
+2. Switch to interval repeat mode, scroll the compact `Weeks` wheel beside its label, choose weekdays/dates, and save `intervalWeeks`.
+3. Render app screens and notifications in English by default and Chinese when the device locale resolves to `zh`.
+
+## Frozen Contracts
+<!-- drift_anchor: frozen_contracts -->
+
+- Hour wheel values remain `0..23`; minute values remain `0..59`; interval week values remain `1..104`.
+- A wheel selection is the value aligned with the wheel center, not the last explicitly tapped item.
+- Wheel controls may still support tapping as a convenience, but tapping is not required to select a scrolled value.
+- Interval week layout is compact: the `Weeks` label and wheel share one horizontal row, and the wheel height is about two rows instead of the main time wheel height.
+- String resources must live in `app/src/main/res/values/strings.xml` for English and `app/src/main/res/values-zh/strings.xml` for Chinese.
+- Compose UI code must use `stringResource` or resource IDs for user-visible copy instead of hardcoded display strings.
+- Android notifications, notification channels, and ringtone picker titles must use `Context.getString(...)`.
+- Locale-sensitive weekday/date display inside composables must remain driven by `LocalConfiguration`, not `Locale.getDefault()`.
+
+## Architecture Invariants
+
+- Wheel UI remains editor-local. It should not leak picker-specific state into the domain layer.
+- ViewModels should not depend on Android `Context` merely to format static UI labels; static labels belong in resources at the composable or Android adapter boundary.
+- Dynamic domain data such as alarm titles, ringtone URIs, model IDs, and remote/provider reasons can remain plain data passed through the UI.
+- Existing test tags can remain stable even when visible text moves to resources.
+
+## Failure Policy
+
+- Invalid picker values should fail fast at the existing ViewModel picker boundary.
+- Missing resource keys should fail at build time.
+- Do not add broad fallback text paths that silently hide missing localization.
+- If a user-facing error includes a remote or exception reason, keep the local surrounding message resource-backed and append the raw reason explicitly.
+
+## Acceptance
+<!-- drift_anchor: acceptance -->
+
+- A Compose/instrumentation test proves scrolling a wheel updates the selected hour/minute without clicking the numeric row.
+- A Compose/instrumentation test proves interval mode shows a compact `Weeks` row and can select an interval week count through the wheel.
+- A resource test proves required English and Chinese string resource files exist and contain matching keys for app UI labels introduced by this scope.
+- Focused editor ViewModel tests still pass.
+- `./gradlew testDebugUnitTest lintDebug assembleDebug` passes.
+- `git diff --check` passes.
+- `PROGRESS.md`, `NEXT_STEP.md`, this spec's plan, and artifact evidence are synchronized before handoff.
+
+## Deferred Decisions
+
+- Add an explicit in-app language picker only after the system locale resource approach is verified.
+- Add locale-aware 12-hour time display only after the 24-hour centered wheel remains stable.
